<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN XXVIII. Vi&#347;vedevas.</h3>  
<p>1. THE Thirty Gods and Three besides, whose seat hath been the sacred grass,<br> From time of old have found and gained.<br> 2 Varu&#7751;a, Mitra, Aryaman, Agnis, with Consorts, sending boons,<br> To whom our Va&#7779;a&#7789;! is addressed:<br> 3 These are our guardians in the west, and northward here, and in the south,<br> And on the cast, with all the tribe.<br> 4 Even as the Gods desire so verily shall it be. None minisheth this power of theirs,<br> No demon, and no mortal<br> 5 The Seven carry seven spears; seven are the splendours they possess,<br> And seven the glories they assume.</p>  
